Rtsne_neighbors compatibility work
----------------------------------

The t-SNE-from-KNN public behaviour was studied against:

  Rtsne
  Authors: Jesse Krijthe, Laurens van der Maaten
  Repository: https://github.com/jkrijthe/Rtsne
  CRAN: https://cran.r-project.org/package=Rtsne
  License: BSD-style license in Rtsne's LICENSE file

The R-level validation/default structure in `R/fast_knn_tsne.R` is adapted
from `Rtsne::Rtsne_neighbors()` and related parameter checking in Rtsne 0.17,
with attribution here and in the source comments.

fastEmbedR does not vendor or copy Rtsne's Barnes-Hut C++ implementation
files (`tsne.cpp`, `tsne.h`, `sptree.cpp`, `sptree.h`, `datapoint.h`,
`vptree.h`). Those upstream files carry the original Delft advertising-clause
BSD license. The current fastEmbedR t-SNE optimizer in `src/tsne_neighbors.cpp`
is package-native code using Rtsne-style KNN affinities, early exaggeration,
momentum, adaptive gains, and zero-mean centering.

Native GPU NN-descent work
--------------------------

The experimental `nn(..., backend = "metal_nndescent")` path adapts the
adaptive NN-descent schedule from:

  mlx-vis
  Author: Han Xiao
  Repository: https://github.com/hanxiao/mlx-vis
  License: Apache-2.0

Specifically, `R/nn.R` and `src/nn.cpp` reuse the high-level ideas from
`mlx_vis/_nndescent/nndescent.py`: NEW/OLD neighbour tracking, adaptive
candidate expansion based on update fraction, reverse-candidate skipping near
convergence, and active-row candidate generation. The implementation is native
R/C++/Metal code for fastEmbedR. It does not vendor mlx-vis source files, link
to mlx-vis, or call Python/MLX at runtime.

The experimental `nn(..., backend = "cuda_nndescent")` path remains native
C++/CUDA code and does not use mlx-vis code.

If future changes copy Apache-2.0 source code into fastEmbedR, keep the
original copyright headers and Apache-2.0 license notices with the copied
source and update this NOTICE file with the exact files/functions used.

